
<sellerabr>ARGYLL</sellerabr> SELLS SUBSIDIARY'S ASSETS FOR <dlramt>14 MLN STG</dlramt>
    LONDON, March 24 - Food and drink retailer <seller>Argyll Group Plc</seller>
{<sellercode>AYLL.L</sellercode>} said it has <status>agreed to sell</status> its U.K. Subsidiary {<acquired>George
Morton Ltd</acquired>} to {<purchaser>Seagram United Kingdom Ltd</purchaser>} for about <dlramt>14 mln
stg</dlramt> in cash.
    The consideration for <acqabr>Morton</acqabr>'s fixed assets, stocks,
debtors and goodwill is payable on completion of the sale. The
disposal will bring Argyll an extraordinary credit of some 8.4
mln stg.
    <sellerabr>Argyll</sellerabr> added the agreements also depend on an indication
from the U.K. Office of Fair Trading by June 23 that the sale
will not be referred to the Monopolies Commission. <sellerabr>Argyll</sellerabr>
shares were up 12p to 440, firming before the announcement.
